com.registry

Class RegDWORDValue

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.registry.RegistryValue
      • com.registry.RegDWORDValue
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Comparable<RegistryValue>

    public class RegDWORDValue
extends RegistryValue

    This class represents a named value of type REG_DWORD, REG_DWORD_LITTLE_ENDIAN, or REG_DWORD_BIG_ENDIAN. The type specific data for the value will be an Integer.

    Version:
    1.8
    Author:
    Yinon Michaeli

    • Method Detail

      • getValue

        public Integer getValue()
        Retrieves the type specific form of this value which is an Integer.

        The Windows Registry uses unsigned integers for DWORDs, so negative values may be returned.

        If the type was changed through a call to RegistryValue.setValueType(ValueType) and is no longer of type REG_DWORD, REG_DWORD_LITTLE_ENDIAN, or REG_DWORD_BIG_ENDIAN, then a RegistryException is thrown.

        If the byte length for the data is not equal to 4, then a RegistryException is also thrown.
        Returns:
        An Integer representing the data.
        Throws:
        RegistryException - if the type is not REG_DWORD, REG_DWORD_LITTLE_ENDIAN, or REG_DWORD_BIG_ENDIAN; or if the byte length is not 4.

      • setValue

        public int setValue(Integer value)
        Used to set the data of this value. If the type is no longer of type REG_DWORD, REG_DWORD_LITTLE_ENDIAN, or REG_DWORD_BIG_ENDIAN, then a RegistryException is thrown.
        Parameters:
        value - An Integer representing the new data for the value.
        Returns:
        An integer error code which tells if the operation was successful or not. To obtain a description of the error, use RegistryKey.formatErrorMessage(int).
        Throws:
        RegistryException - if the type is not REG_DWORD, REG_DWORD_LITTLE_ENDIAN, or REG_DWORD_BIG_ENDIAN.
